# Build context exclusions for Docker builds.
#
# Without this file, `docker compose build` ships the ENTIRE repo to
# the daemon — on this repo that's ~2 GB of `.venv/` + `node_modules/`
# + git history that the build never reads. Excluding them shaves
# 1-3 minutes off every build on macOS Docker Desktop, where the
# build context crosses the FUSE bridge from macOS to the Linux VM.
#
# Pattern syntax mirrors `.gitignore`. The Dockerfile only needs:
#   * pyproject.toml + README.md   (early COPY for dep cache)
#   * src/                         (Python source)
#   * deploy/                      (entrypoint scripts)
# Everything else is dead weight.

# ---- Python virtual envs (the big one) ----------------------------
# Local .venv is 1.5-2 GB on a developer laptop. The Dockerfile
# rebuilds its own venv inside the image; the host one is
# irrelevant.
.venv/
venv/
env/
.python-version

# ---- Python build artefacts ---------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
*.egg
build/
dist/
.eggs/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.tox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/

# ---- Node / frontend ----------------------------------------------
# Frontend is built in its own multi-stage block in
# deploy/dev/docker-compose.yml; the worker/api image never reads it.
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
frontend/.vite/
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*

# ---- Git / SCM ----------------------------------------------------
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# ---- Docker (don't recurse into compose state) --------------------
# Compose project state Docker writes into the repo on macOS.
# Including these in the context loops the build through its own
# output dir.
deploy/dev/.docker/

# ---- Local dev state ----------------------------------------------
data/
logs/
*.log
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env1

# ---- Editor / IDE -------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ---- CI / repo metadata -------------------------------------------
.github/
.claude/
.cursor/
.continue/

# ---- Documentation (image doesn't serve it) -----------------------
docs/
*.md
!README.md

# ---- Tests (not needed in runtime image) --------------------------
tests/
